the last 9 months."\n\nOn 6 Nowoniner 3008, the Office of the Chartcellor directed respondent to submit been which she did on 11 November 2008, in this wise.\n\nI admit that I did once become an irresponsible Sloyce Turing the critical times of my life, but it is also the know reverybody that I was serving the institute constituents for many years with all my heart."\n\n"2. My absence started when my husband Mr. Delcon died.\n\n"3. Since September 23, 2008 Falready reported for work."', '"2. My absence started when my husband Mr. Delcon died.\n\n"3. Since September 23, 2008 Falready reported for work."\n\nA careful scrutiny of the documents adduced by Dr. Abragan, considered in the light of the unqualified admission of respondent, will indubitably establish a prima facie case against the latter.\n\n· The records show that respondent has been consistently absent from work from Ianuary to September 2008, for 110 days, without an approved A-151\n\nAnnex " UH-4 "\n\nRepublic of the Philippines ILIGAN INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY of the Mindanao State University\n\n### LEGAL SERVICES OFFICE\n\nA. Benifacio Avenue, 9209 Higan City Icl. Nos. (063) 351-6174 (191 ) (063) 221-4050 -55 (11.) 1.0cal-175\n\nleave. This fact is reinforced by the apparent tailure of respondent to fill up her daily time record. Thus, she could be dropped from the rolls for being absent without an approved leave for more than thirty (30) days.', 'On 26 November 2008, the Chancellor issued a formal charge pursuant to Civil Service Commission {CSC} Resolution No. 991936, directing respondent to answer the indictment against her within 72 hours from receipt thereof.\n\nOn 2 December 2009, respondent tendered her mayer/rep where she admitted the material allegations against her but at he was . - The requested a full blown investigation. Consequently, the Chrincellor saled Special Order No. 00899, Series of 2008, creating a Disciplinary > > mith > composed of the undersigned, to conduct a formal probe on are che for habitual and frequent unauthorized absences, inefficie cy, incoupelence, and conduct prejudicial to the best interest of the service - sinst the respondent.', "On H December 2008, a smal saring was conducted by the Committee in the presence of the respondent's immediate supervisor, Dr. Ruby G. Abragan. The Committe offormed respondent of her right to be represented by counsel of her chose considering the gravity of the accusations. Respondent kos the probe sans representation\n\nDuring the crimal in estigation, respondent admitted that her unauthorized absences - we wased by her personal problems arising from the death of her husbane in 2003. However, the Committee notes that respondent started her m = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = five [5] years from the demise of her husband. In other words, the death of her husband in 2003 w is not the proximate cause for her frequent absences begin ong Januar 1 2008.", "Furthermore, records also show that respondent's absences were neither authorized nor approved by her immediate superior. It is worthy to note that under CSC Memorandum Circular No. 4, Series of 1991, an officer or employce in the Civil Service shall be considered habitually absent it he/she incurs unauthorized absences exceeding the allowable 2.5 days monthly leave credits under the leave law for at least three (3) months in a semester or at least three (3) consecutive months during the year. Such a violation renders the erring employee administratively liable for grave offense of Frequent Unauthorized Absences in Reporting for Duty and for Gross Neglect of Duty under Section 22 (g) and (a), respectively of the Omnibus Rules Implementing Book V of Executive Order No. 292.\n\nesolution No. 73, S. 2009\n\nRepublic of the Philippines ILIGAN INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY of the Mindanao State University\n\nLEGAL SERVICES OFFICE", "esolution No. 73, S. 2009\n\nRepublic of the Philippines ILIGAN INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY of the Mindanao State University\n\nLEGAL SERVICES OFFICE\n\nA. Bonifacio Avenue, 9200 Higan City Tel. Nos. (063) 354-6174 (DI.) (063) 221-4050-55 (11) 1 och| 175\n\nWhile we would like to empathize with respondent however we cannot close our eyes to the undeniable fact that her unauthorized absences caused prejudice to public service.\n\nMSU BOARD OF Rundon .. 3\n\nThe seriousness of the charge, coupled with respondent's unqualified admission thereto, prompted the Committee to suggest that she avail of an early relirement from the service. But respondent re--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------", 'As a result of Ms. Bola\'s frequent abser. John facted to perform her duties and responsibilities in the government service. Every time respondent absents herself without permission, she a. Neces willy neglects performing her duties at the Clinic. This has been ing - time and again for nine (9) long months, consisting of 110 days to be excel. By her own admission, respondent has been temiss, as a pu "ic servent, in the performance of Her duties, Indeed, even with the ful. \\ me. \\_\\_ e of sympathy and patience, we cantiot act otherwise since the carger. Sept government service cannot the should never be subordinate to percely human equations.', 'WHEREFORE, the Commits & linds respondent guilty of habitual and frequent imauthorized as acreat of 110 days, committed from January to Septer - 2008 inefficiency; incompetence; and, conduct prejudicial to the best c erest of the service. Considering however that respondent upco. "Gonal 7 admitted her guilt (which is appreciated as a mitigating circa stance and considering further that she served the hustifule for twenty - fine Q years, the Committee hereby recommends a penally of suspension - thout pay for a period of eight [8] months, with a stern warning that a resertition if similar conduct or any violation of civil service rules and reg (ations n. the future will merif a more/severe penalty.\n\nIngan City, 18 February 2009. . Roberto C /11/4 Chairman Ms. Monawira A. Ali Ms. Many (J. Nirio Member No Dr. Rhodora S. N. Englis Prof. Gobffrey G. Salgado Member Momber']
